            "description": "## Get User By ID\n\nRetrieves the details of a specific user identified by their unique ID.\n\n### Endpoint\n\n```\nGET {{endpoint}}user/2\n\n ```\n\nThe `{{endpoint}}` variable represents the base URL of the API and should be defined in the active Postman environment (e.g., `https://api.example.com/`).\n\n### URL Structure\n\n| Segment | Description |\n| --- | --- |\n| `{{endpoint}}` | Base URL, resolved from the active environment variable |\n| `user/` | Resource path targeting the users collection |\n| `2` | The ID of the user to retrieve (currently hardcoded as `2`; replace with the desired user's ID) |\n\n### Path Parameter\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `id` | integer | The unique identifier of the target user. Currently set to `2`. |\n\n### Expected Response\n\nOn success, the endpoint returns a **200 OK** status along with a JSON object containing the details of the requested user, such as:\n\n``` json\n{\n    \"id\": 2,\n    \"name\": \"User 2\",\n    \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-20T03:42:36.319723Z\",\n    \"updatedAt\": \"2026-04-20T03:42:36.319723Z\"\n}\n\n ```\n\n> **Note:** The user ID is hardcoded as `2` in the current URL. To query a different user, update the path with the appropriate user ID or use a path variable (e.g., `{{endpoint}}user/{{userId}}`)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
