            "description": "## DeleteUserById\n\nDeletes a specific user from the system by their unique ID.\n\n### Endpoint\n\n```\nDELETE {{endpoint}}user/:id\n```\n\n### Path Parameter\n\n| Parameter | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `id` | The unique identifier of the user to delete. In the current request, `10` is used as the user ID. |\n\n### Successful Response\n\nA successful request typically returns one of the following:\n\n- **`200 OK`** — The user was deleted, and the server returns a confirmation body.\n- **`204 No Content`** — The user was deleted successfully, with no response body.\n\n### Notes\n\n> ⚠️ **This action is irreversible.** Once a user is deleted, the data cannot be recovered. Ensure the correct user ID is provided before sending the request."
          },
